<span>LinkedIn</span>
</a><a class=social-link href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&amp;user=dQw8Wr4AAAAJ" target=_blank rel=noopener aria-label="Google Scholar"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 3 1 9l11 6 9-4.91V17h2V9L12 3zM5 13.18v4L12 21l7-3.82v-4L12 17l-7-3.82z"/></svg>
<span>Google Scholar</span></a></div><div class=hero-credentials><p class=hero-credentials-label>Featured, backed, and recognised by</p><ul class=hero-credentials-list><li>Schwarzman Scholars</li><li>Arrington Capital</li><li>Protocol Labs (YC S14)</li><li>SpaceX Hyperloop</li><li>ETHGlobal</li><li>UN ECOSOC</li><li>Cointelegraph</li></ul></div></div></div></section><section class=scope><div class=container><h2>What I work on</h2><div class=scope-grid><div class=scope-item><h3>DePIN and Blockchain Infrastructure</h3><p>Co-Founder & CSO at Titan Network. The Decentralized Cloud Platform for enterprise scale, that provides access to enterprise-grade Proxy infrastructure, CDN, Web Scraping and Storage powered by a global digital resource network, while cutting cloud & data collection costs by up to 80%.</p><a href=https://titannet.io>Titan Network →</a></div><div class=scope-item><h3>Civic Leadership & Global Impact</h3><p>Co-Founder & COO of Future International Foundation, a NYC-based 501(c)(3) on equal youth access to education and UN Sustainable Development Goals. 200+ members across 70+ countries, 20+ high-level events. Recommended for UN ECOSOC Special Consultative Status (Feb 2026).</p><a href=https://www.futureinternational.org/>Future International Foundation →</a></div><div class=scope-item><h3>Startup Advisory & Security Consulting</h3><p>Advising 10+ Web3 startups from founding to Series B on BD, fundraising, technical architecture, and tokenomics design, with successful raises in every engagement. Security and economic-model audit work with Collectif Labs on Lido's dual-governance parameters, across Filecoin, Ethereum, and Avalanche ecosystems.</p><ul class=scope-links><li><a href=/about/>About →</a></li><li><a href=https://github.com/lidofinance/dual-governance/blob/develop/docs/dg-params-research-by-collectif-labs.pdf>Lido Audit (PDF) →</a></li><li><a href=https://research.lido.fi/t/dual-governance-analytics-note-on-parameters-values/9905>Lido Research Forum →</a></li></ul></div><div class=scope-item><h3>Web3, AI and Economics Research</h3><p>Multistakeholder governance research (Tsinghua / Schwarzman, Outstanding Thesis Award), ongoing article writing, and peer-reviewed publications on AI in construction, embedded energy, and sustainability. Research interests span Web3, AI, Civil Engineering, and Sustainability. 118+ citations on Google Scholar.</p><ul class=scope-links><li><a href=/about/#publications>Published works →</a></li><li><a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&amp;user=dQw8Wr4AAAAJ">Google Scholar →</a></li><li><a href=/writing/>Writings →</a></li></ul></div></div></div></section><section class=split-section><div class=container><div class=split-inner><div class=split-left><div><h2>Publication and Media</h2></div><a class=split-arrow href=/writing/ aria-label="View all writings"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="7" y1="17" x2="17" y2="7"/><polyline points="7 7 17 7 17 17"/></svg></a></div><div class=split-right><div class=split-block><h3>Academic Research and Publications</h3><p>Peer-reviewed research across Web3 governance, AI, civil engineering, and sustainability (118+ citations on Google Scholar). Schwarzman Scholar at Tsinghua, where my capstone under Prof. Ronaldo Lemos earned the Outstanding Thesis Award. Co-founded Future International Foundation, recommended for UN ECOSOC consultative status, keeping technology development anchored in broader societal contexts.</p><ul class=block-links><li><a href=/about/#publications>Publications on About page →</a></li><li><a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&amp;user=dQw8Wr4AAAAJ">Google Scholar →</a></li></ul></div><div class=split-block><h3>Technical Papers, Security Audits and Articles</h3><p>Protocol design and tokenomics documented through Titan Network's whitepaper and lightpaper. Audit research on Lido's dual-governance parameters in collaboration with Collectif Labs. Long-form writing on DePIN economics, blockchain governance, and Web3 infrastructure published here and across social channels.</p><ul class=block-links><li><a href=/writing/>Writings →</a></li><li><a href=https://whitepaper.titannet.io>Titan Network Whitepaper →</a></li><li><a href=https://lightpaper.titannet.io>Titan Network Lightpaper →</a></li><li><a href=https://github.com/lidofinance/dual-governance/blob/develop/docs/dg-params-research-by-collectif-labs.pdf>Lido Dual-Governance Research (PDF) →</a></li><li><a href=https://www.linkedin.com/in/tkachukk/>LinkedIn →</a></li><li><a href=https://twitter.com/tkachuk_science>Twitter →</a></li></ul></div><div class=split-block><h3>Talks, Events, Podcasts</h3><p>Regular contributions to DePIN Day, FIL Bangkok, ETHGlobal, and industry podcasts across Web3, AI, and sustainability topics. 50+ talks, panels, and podcasts over the last two years, ranging from the politics of decentralised infrastructure to enterprise adoption and the practical mechanics of building.</p><a class=block-link href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0r1L6VofcJE&amp;list=PLzs_2PoZkZONvnZm4juzQXGBKzUeEA6XD&amp;index=20">YouTube playlist →</a></div></div></div></div></section><section class=latest-highlight aria-label="Latest Highlight"><div class=container><p class=latest-highlight-label>Latest Highlight</p><article class=highlight-card><div class=highlight-body><p class=highlight-meta><span class=highlight-kind>Article</span> · <time>April 2026</time></p><h3 class=highlight-title>DePIN Is Dead. Long Live DePIN.</h3><p class=highlight-desc>Only two DePIN projects crossed $1M in annualized non-token revenue before 2024. What broke, who survived by becoming different businesses, and why the service layer always wins.</p><a class=highlight-link href=/writing/depin-is-dead-long-live-depin/>Read → →</a></div></article></div></section><section class=card-row><div class=container><div class=card-row-header><h2>Latest Videos</h2><a class=row-link href=/speaking/>View all →</a></div><div class=video-row><article class=media-card><a class="thumb has-play" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4bGVPVD2WTA" aria-label="Play: Titan Network: Building the Edge from Idle Devices" style=background-image:url(https://img.youtube.com/vi/4bGVPVD2WTA/hqdefault.jpg)></a><div class=media-card-body><span class=media-meta>Oct 2025</span><h3>Titan Network: Building the Edge from Idle Devices</h3><p>How Titan turns idle phones and laptops into a global edge cloud — CDN, AI, and Web2-scale services across 130+ countries. DePIN Day Singapore 2025.</p></div></article><article class=media-card><a class="thumb has-play" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1dtvhvSmo3E" aria-label="Play: DePIN for TikTok, $1M Revenue & 550K Devices" style=background-image:url(https://img.youtube.com/vi/1dtvhvSmo3E/hqdefault.jpg)></a><div class=media-card-body><span class=media-meta>2024</span><h3>DePIN for TikTok, $1M Revenue & 550K Devices</h3><p>Deep dive into Titan's demand-first growth, dynamic incentives, real enterprise revenue, and the road to mainnet.</p></div></article><article class=media-card><a class="thumb has-play" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4ht4dghFbjA" aria-label="Play: Titan Network: Leveraging Idle Resources for Decentralised Compute" style=background-image:url(https://img.youtube.com/vi/4ht4dghFbjA/hqdefault.jpg)></a><div class=media-card-body><span class=media-meta>2024</span><h3>Titan Network: Leveraging Idle Resources for Decentralised Compute</h3><p>Building the incentive layer for global idle resources. DePIN economics, edge computing, and 50-80% cost savings over traditional cloud.</p></div></article></div></div></section><section class=newsletter-cta><div class=container><p class=newsletter-kicker>Monthly newsletter</p><h2>Read what I'm actually building.</h2><p>One email a month. Long-form analysis on DePIN, blockchain governance, and what it takes to ship infrastructure. No hype, no price calls, no partnership announcements with nothing behind them.</p><form class="newsletter-form js-ajax-form" action=/api/subscribe method=POST><label for=newsletter-email class=sr-only>Email address</label>
